        "title": "See also"
      },
      {
        "blocks": [
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "The arithmetic mean is the sum of the non-NaN elements along the axis\ndivided by the number of non-NaN elements."
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          },
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "Note that for floating-point input, the mean is computed using the same\nprecision the input has.  Depending on the input data, this can cause\nthe results to be inaccurate, especially for "
              },
              {
                "kind": "code",
                "text": "float32"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": ".  Specifying a\nhigher-precision accumulator using the "
              },
              {
                "kind": "code",
                "text": "dtype"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": " keyword can alleviate\nthis issue."
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          }
        ],
        "title": "Notes"
      },
